# Security Rules

## Supabase — Non-negotiable

- **Every new table must have RLS enabled** before any data is inserted. No exceptions.
- **Always create RLS policies** alongside table creation. A table with RLS enabled but no policies blocks all access — verify policies work.
- **Never use the service role key in client-side code.** Only the anon key (`SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`) is allowed in frontend code. The service role key is restricted to Edge Functions or server-side code.
- **Never expose environment variables** (service keys, secrets) in client bundles. Use `VITE_` or `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefixes only for public values (anon key, Supabase URL).

## File Storage

- **No public buckets.** All file access uses signed URLs with expiration.
- **Validate file types and size** on upload — both client-side and server-side.

## Sync & Auth

- **Every sync request** from Dexie.js to Supabase must include a valid Supabase Auth token. No anonymous writes.
- **Validate auth server-side** in Edge Functions — never trust the client token without verification.

## Data & Input

- **Validate all input** client-side (UX) and server-side (security). Never trust the client.
- **Sanitize** any user-provided text before rendering to prevent XSS.
- **Financial amounts** should use integer arithmetic (centavos, not pesos with decimals) to avoid floating-point errors.

## Local Storage (Dexie.js / IndexedDB)

- Local data is **unencrypted**. Acceptable for single-user MVP.
- If multi-user or sensitive third-party data is stored, encrypt with Web Crypto API before writing to IndexedDB.
